entry.title: Deflake MediaStreamTrack-video-stats.https.html.
entry.content:
A test was recently added which asserts that frames are frozen during a

task execution cycle. But it also asserted that after 100 ms and one

task execution cycle later, the frame counter would have incremented.



This is a reasonable assumption on a fast machine, but the WPT waterfall

can be really slow in which case no frame is produced in 100 ms and the

test flakily failed, see recent failures at

https://ci.chromium.org/ui/p/chromium/builders/ci/mac12-arm64-rel-tests



It's best to just remove this assertion. Other tests already cover

"wait for frame counters to increment" without a time limit, so there is

no need to relax it here and we don't want to increase the time that it

blocks...

entry.title: Records the number of sources per source origin on DB initialization
entry.content:
We currently have a limit on the number of sources per source origin. To

better understand the impact on disk usage of this limit, we want to

understand the distribution that follows the number of sources per

source origin.



In this CL we add four histograms that correspond to the number of

sources per source origin for the nth ranked source origin.



- Conversions.SourcesPerSourceOrigin.1st

- Conversions.SourcesPerSourceOrigin.3rd

- Conversions.SourcesPerSourceOrigin.7th

- Conversions.SourcesPerSourceOrigin.20th



The number of selected positions and their ranks is somewhat arbitrary

but they were picked to have sufficient samples from the distribution

while limiting the number of histograms added.

entry.title: [webauthn] List phones for non rk requests if no creds found
entry.content:
With the new UI, phones are not listed on the webauthn UI if the user is

opted in to syncing webauthn credentials under the assumption that

generally, having no credentials synced means the user cannot use that

phone (they can still scan a QR code if needed, e.g. because of sync

delay).



However, for allow-list requests, non discoverable credentials that will

never sync are applicable. This CL updates Chrome to list phones for

allow-list requests when Chrome has not found any synced passkeys,

restoring the ease of use of those credentials in a second factor

setting.

entry.title: Portals: Cancel drag-drop in predecessor before activation
entry.content:
We have existing drag-drop checks that prevent data from a

cross-site subframe from being transferred to the main frame, but

these break with portal activation. With portal activation we have two

problems:



1) Portal activation causes a switch in WebContents, and we currently

don't restrict drag and drops across WebContents (as dragging

across tabs is considered to be sufficient user-intent). However,

in this case, portals are within the same tab, and allowing a

cross-origin drag-and-drop across portal activation has the

same security risks outlined in https://crbug.com/59081 and

https://crbug.com/1264873.



2) Portal activation, adoption and reactivation can result in the

WebContentsViewAura being reset and recreated, so the |drag_start_|

field will be reset. We can have a portal being activated, the

predecessor being adopted, and then reactivated, all while a

drag-drop is active, and the resulting drop's checks will be

bypassed (within the same page) as |drag_start_| is reset and is

now absl::nullopt [1].



[1] https://source.chromium.org/chromium/chromium/src/+/main:content/browser/web_contents/web_contents_view_aura.cc;l=855;drc=c2cca37e05cb5b20019a27406714d1954194c2d4



To fix this, we explicitly cancel a drag-drop before activating a

portal. This disallows a drag-drop for persisting across portal

activation. The predecessor page becomes a portal and doesn't allow

input events at that point, and drag and drop failing shouldn't be unexpected behaviour.



Note: This only fixes the issue on Aura; but this likely needs a fix

for Mac as well, which will be in a follow up.

entry.title: Fix logic to prevent multiple calls to ApplyAddressFixesAndCleanups for sync-the-transport
entry.content:
ApplyAddressFixesAndCleanups and ApplyCardFixesAndCleanups has multiple

call sites.

[1] From PersonalDataManagerCleaner::CleanupDataAndNotifyPersonalDataObservers

[2] PersonalDataManagerCleaner::SyncStarted



The call from [2] should happen if the user is syncing and have enabled the type in sync-the-feature mode or if the user enabled the relevant user selectable in the sync-the-transport mode.



The call from [1] should happen in all the other cases where the user

is not syncing at all or the user has not enabled the type.



Prior to this CL, there would be calls from both [1] and [2] to the

ApplyAddressFixesAndCleanups in sync-the-transport mode when the user

would have enabled the user selectable type as

`sync_service_->IsSyncFeatureEnabled()` would return false in this case.

This CL ensures that in this case, the call happens from only [2].



Also, the ApplyAddressFixesAndCleanups should happen once both the

AUTOFILL_PROFILE and CONTACT_INFO sync has started as the dedupe logic

uses the contact info profiles for removing the duplicate local profile.

entry.title: Wait 500ms before retrying to restore the context
entry.content:
In case of failure to restore the context, the

CanvasRenderingContext2D::TryRestoreContextEvent method was retrying

right away, by calling itself recursively. If the function has just

failed, there is no reason it should succeed by merely calling it once

more.



The original logic of this method was to wait for 500ms between retries.

This has been changed in https://crrev.com/c/2932376. This CL restores

that behavior and applies it to the offscreen canvas as well.

entry.content:
This is a refactoring CL to unify the LcppData load path to one.

It starts to return a data structure for LcppData, and makes

operations on frequencies happens on demand when Predict* methods

entry.title: Fix client window freeze when starting gestures with more than 2 fingers
entry.content:
When a gesture with more than 2 fingers (e.g. 3-finger pinch) starts on

a client window (e.g. Lacros PiP window), it leads to an inconsistent

state and the window becomes immovable until the window is closed.



This commit removes the code that was updating the `gesture_target_` to

`nullptr` in `ToplevelWindowEventHandler::CompleteDrag()`.

`gesture_target_` should not be updated to `nullptr` in `CompleteDrag()`

because:



- the existence of `gesture_target_` is used elsewhere to determine if

an ongoing event has originated from a touchscreen or a mouse, and



- `CompleteDrag()` is called even when a gesture hasn't completely ended

(i.e. when at least one finger is still on the screen, like when a

more-than-2-finger gesture starts).



If the gesture successfully completes then

`UpdateGestureTarget(nullptr)` is called when the last finger leaves the

screen in `ToplevelWindowEventHandler` anyways, so it should be

unnecessary to call it in `CompleteDrag()`.



Bug: b/301013053

Test: manually verified that the window stays movable after

more-than-2-finger gestures

entry.title: Add tests to confirm the network error in ServiceWorkerAutoPreload
entry.content:
This CL adds a unit test for the network error case in

ServiceWorkerAutoPreload. We had a crash bug due to the unexpected

state transition from State::kResponseReceived to State::kCompleted.

This was fixed in [1], but the test was not added. The new unit test in

this CL confirms the transition works as intended.



This transition could happen when below conditions are all met:

1) SWAutoPreload is enabled.

2) The fetch handler result is fallback.

3) The initial response is successfully received.

4) The response is not transered into the data pipe yet for teeing.

5) The response is completed with the network error.

entry.title: Improve column balancing for IFC-floats.
entry.content:
Space shortage caused by float breaks wasn't propagated correctly for

floats inside an inline formatting context, resulting in column

balancing problems, typically over-stretching.



Let PositionFloat() create a break-before break token, instead of

requiring every call site to do it. Also propagate space shortage here.



This required that space shortage propagation code were moved up from

NGBoxFragmentBuilder to NGFragmentBuilder, so that it can be used with

NGLineBoxFragmentBuilder can use it as well. Since this is closely tied

with another column balancing concept - tallest unbreakable block-size -

also move that one.



Add two tests: One for floats as block children. This was already

working, but there was no test coverage. The other test is for floats as

inline children, and this wasn't working without this CL.

Reason for revert: Gardening: Multiple PDFExtensionAccessibilityTreeDumpTest tests are failing.



See https://crbug.com/1484882



Original change's description:

> PDF a11y: Create the status node to notify users of PDF content loading

>

> Make the status node available regardless of the PDF OCR feature to

> notify users of PDF content loading. This status node will be added and

> become available when it starts to load PDF content into an a11y tree.

> Then, the status node will be deleted once it finishes loading the

> PDF content into the tree.

>

> Note that this status node will be kept when PDF OCR is on and PDF

> doesn't have accessible text but images without alternative text.

>

> This notification is necessary especially when users open a large PDF

> (e.g. 200 or more pages) as it takes one or more minutes to load such

> a large PDF. Without notification, users won't have any accessible

> information that helps them know what's going on after opening a PDF

> until it finishes loading the PDF content into an a11y tree.
